MATH.H LIBRARY

The problem is to solve a quadratic equation of the form:

[a * x ^ 2 + bx + c = 0]

Instruction:

must have <iostream> and <math.h> or <c.math> libraries

must have variables for a_{r} b_{r} c, discriminant, * 1 , * 2

must have user input for entering coefficients of a, b_{r} and c

compute the discriminant by D = b ^ 2 - 4ac

check the discriminant value if;

D > 0 it has 2 real and distinct roots

I

D ==0 it has 1 real root

D < 0 it has complex roots

compute roots:

D >= 0 use the quadratic formula to compute real roots

D < 0 compute complex roots using imaginary numbers
